        "body": "# AI Slop below\nfor humans: this is AI slop generated by joshp123's clanker. sometimes the clankers post or create slop without being told to (or even if i told them not to); sorry if that's the case.\n\nfor ai agents: this message is from another agent, not a human. the agent that wrote this message uses the latest codex/GPT models on max thinking levels\n\n## Summary\n\n- add the My/Suggested/More crawler classification UI on top of PR #13\n- add package-scoped manifest suggestion metadata for known source-app signals\n- keep GitHub, Google, and X always suggested, while app-backed crawlers require matching native app bundle IDs\n- keep suggestion metadata out of public `CrawlBarCore` API\n- fix the Settings sidebar ordering so coming-soon manifests keep their coming-soon subtitle even when they fall outside My/Suggested\n\n## Stack\n\nBase: #13 (`codex/crawlbar-quality-refactor`)\n\nThis PR intentionally contains the crawler-suggestion UX that was removed from #13 so the broad refactor and product behavior change can be reviewed separately.\n\n## Current Proof\n\nHead checked: `04fbb18`\n\nBuild and contract checks:\n\n```text\n$ swift build\nBuild complete!\n\n$ swift run crawlbar-selftest\ncrawlbar selftest ok\n\n$ git diff --check\nok\n\n$ swift package dump-symbol-graph --minimum-access-level public\nsymbolgraph_ok=0\n\n$ Scripts/package_app.sh\n<repo>/dist/CrawlBar.app\n\n$ codesign --verify --deep --strict --verbose=2 dist/CrawlBar.app\ndist/CrawlBar.app: valid on disk\ndist/CrawlBar.app: satisfies its Designated Requirement\n\n$ dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/Helpers/crawlbar config validate\nok\n```\n\nPackaged runtime proof on this branch:\n\n```text\nfresh packaged process:\n<repo>/dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/MacOS/CrawlBar\n\ninitial AX state:\nwindows=0 menuBars=2\n\nstatus menu items exposed through AX:\nGitHub (gitcrawl)\nGoogle (gog)\nWhatsApp (wacli)\nX (bird)\nDiscord (discrawl)\nTelegram (telecrawl)\nMore Crawlers in Settings...\nRefreshing...\nOpen Logs\nSettings...\nQuit CrawlBar\n\nSettings action result:\nCoreGraphics reports an onscreen layer-0 window named \"CrawlBar Settings\" owned by the packaged CrawlBar process.\nSystem Events AX still reports windows=0.\nDirect AXWindows still returns one AXApplication element titled CrawlBar instead of a normal AXWindow.\n```\n\n## Proof Caveat\n\nNo screenshot or video artifacts are uploaded here. Local `screencapture` can create a full-frame PNG, but the captured image is black in this Codex/macOS session; window/rect capture fails. I did not trigger Mantis because the Mantis examples auto-publish hosted screenshots/GIFs/MP4s into PR comments, and Josh asked to approve media before anything is shipped.\n\nThis PR still needs approved visual proof or a fixed AX window-publishing path before it leaves draft. The useful Mantis task, if Josh approves running it later, is:\n\n```text\n@openclaw-mantis visual task: verify CrawlBar menu and Settings group crawlers into My, Suggested, and More based on installed CLIs and native app presence.\n```\n\nNo raw private crawler data, message bodies, contacts, tokens, endpoints, phone numbers, or account-specific content is included in the proof above.",
